# Project rules for AI agents

## Code style

- TypeScript: stay strict; avoid `any` unless there is a clear, narrow reason.
- React: functional components and hooks; keep state and effects easy to follow.
- Names and functions: descriptive, small, single-purpose.

## Stack & tooling

- **React 19** + **TypeScript** + **Vite 8** (`@vitejs/plugin-react`), ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.js`).
- After substantive changes, run **`npm run lint`** and **`npm run build`**; fix anything introduced by the edit.
- Scripts: `npm run dev`, `npm run build`, `npm run preview`, `npm run lint`.

## Product context — simple-name-picker

- Front-end app for **random picking** from a name catalog with **ratings** (like/dislike), **bans** (skipped until restored), and **browser persistence** (`localStorage`, key `simple-name-picker:names` in `src/namesStorage.ts`).
- **Discarded (banned) UI** lists `discardedNames`: bans **intersected** with the current `names` catalog. Intro copy and counts should stay consistent with that list (not raw `banned.length`, which can include orphaned entries).
- After **like/dislike**, the picker **advances** to another random pickable name when possible (see `useNamePicker`).
- Prefer **simple, accessible UI** (keyboard, labels, readable contrast).

## Editing habits

- Prefer changing existing files over adding new ones when it keeps the design clear.
- Match indentation and formatting already in the file.
- Do not add dependencies without a short justification; keep the repo lightweight unless product needs say otherwise.

## Project structure

- Entry: `src/main.tsx`, shell: `src/App.tsx`.
- UI: `src/components/` (this repo uses per-component folders with `index.tsx` + co-located CSS where needed).
- Logic: `src/hooks/` (`usePersistedNamesCatalog`, `useNamePicker`, `useStatusMessage`), `src/namePickerState.ts`, `src/namesStorage.ts`.
- Default catalog: `src/data/names.ts` (sourced from `raw-names-list.md` when regenerated).
- Styles: `src/*.css`, `public/` for static assets.
- **Changelog:** [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) at repo root (`CHANGELOG.md`); update it for user-visible fixes and behavior changes.

## Commit messages

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/):

`type[optional scope]: description`

- **feat:** — new feature (MINOR)
- **fix:** — bug fix (PATCH)
- **docs:** / **style:** / **refactor:** / **perf:** / **test:** / **chore:** — as usual
- **BREAKING CHANGE:** `!` after type/scope or footer for MAJOR

Example: `feat: add name list editor`

## Versioning & changelog

- **SemVer** in `package.json` when cutting releases.
- Maintain **`CHANGELOG.md`** at repo root ([Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/)); add **Unreleased** notes for notable fixes/features, then cut dated version sections when releasing.
- **README.md** should stay aligned with real behavior (persistence key, main flows, layout).
- **Vite `define` / build-time version strings:** only add when the UI or logic needs them.

## Communication

- Be direct and concise.
- If requirements are ambiguous, ask before large refactors.
- Briefly note non-obvious choices in responses or commits.
